<p>I have this form,  and on this form, I have a control, this control is a datepicker. It looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="form-group" ng-class="{ 'has-error' : !orderLine.required.$pristine &amp;&amp; orderLine.required.$invalid || !orderLine.required }"&gt;     &lt;label class="control-label"&gt;Required date&lt;/label&gt;     &lt;div class="input-group"&gt;         &lt;input class="form-control" type="text" name="required" ng-model="controller.orderLine.dates.required" datepicker-popup show-weeks="false" is-open="controller.calendar.open" required /&gt;         &lt;span class="input-group-btn"&gt;             &lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-default" ng-click="controller.openCalendar($event)"&gt;&lt;span class="fa fa-calendar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt;         &lt;/span&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;     valid: {{ !orderLine.required.$invalid }} &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>As you can see, this is a required field. If I pull in some data from the server and populate this field with the value, the control is still marked as invalid. Does anyone know why?</p>